<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="83.[128,654,211,1759]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
COMMENTS: In his report on the 1928– 1929 collection made by Ernst Mayr in what was at that time northern Dutch New 
<collectingCountry box="[128,216,506,528]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" box="[230,485,507,529]" firstAuthor="Hartert" page="29 - 30" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="27 - 128" refId="ref126116" refString="Hartert, E. 1930. III. List of the birds collected by Ernst Mayr. Novitates Zoologicae 36: 27 - 128." type="journal article" year="1930">Hartert (1930: 29–30)</bibRefCitation>
addressed the problem of whether males of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schlegel" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Aves" family="Ptilonorhynchidae" genus="Amblyornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inornatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Amblyornis inornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possessed the orange crest of forms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D.G.Elliot" authorityYear="1872" box="[171,302,594,617]" class="Aves" family="Ptilonorhynchidae" genus="Amblyornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[171,302,594,617]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Amblyornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from farther east in New 
<collectingCountry box="[128,217,624,646]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. None of Mayr’s recently collected specimens from the Arfak area and the mountains of the Wandammen Peninsula had crests, nor had others from the Arfak that were well-labeled as to locality. The Rothschild Collection held a number of ‘‘trade-skins’’ with unreliable or no collecting locality that did possess crests. Hartert named a crested form supposed to be from Karon, northern Vogelkop, 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Ptilonorhynchidae" genus="Amblyornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="inornatus" subSpecies="mayri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Amblyornis inornatus mayri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There are only two specimens labeled with the locality ‘‘Karon’’ in AMNH, and I have considered both of them 
<typeStatus box="[547,650,975,996]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Although the Rothschild type label is tied on AMNH 679526, it is only on the label of the other, AMNH 679525, that there is a note: ‘‘Bought from Renesse van Duivenbode 1895.’’ Although both were probably purchased from him, only this specimen gives the date mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" box="[372,599,1180,1202]" firstAuthor="Hartert" page="29" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="27 - 128" refId="ref126116" refString="Hartert, E. 1930. III. List of the birds collected by Ernst Mayr. Novitates Zoologicae 36: 27 - 128." type="journal article" year="1930">Hartert (1930: 29)</bibRefCitation>
. An AMNH type label has been added to AMNH 679525. This name was introduced too late to have been included in any of Hartert’s lists of types in the Rothschild Collection. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Mayr" firstAuthor="Mayr" page="23 - 25" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="20 - 26" refId="ref130097" refString="Mayr, E. 1930 a. My Dutch New Guinea expedition, 1928. Novitates Zoologicae 36: 20 - 26." type="journal article" year="1930" yearSuffix="a">Mayr (1930a: 23–25)</bibRefCitation>
for an account of Mayr’s expedition into the Arfak Mountains and mountains of the Wandammen Peninsula.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="83.[128,654,211,1759]" lastBlockId="83.[701,1228,213,293]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" box="[157,445,1415,1437]" firstAuthor="Rothschild" page="251" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="250 - 276" refId="ref135020" refString="Rothschild, W. 1931. On a collection of birds made by Mr. F. Shaw Mayer in the Weyland Mountans, Dutch New Guinea, in 1930. Novitates Zoologicae 36: 250 - 276." type="journal article" year="1931">Rothschild (1931: 251)</bibRefCitation>
, reporting on a collection of birds made by Fred Shaw Mayer in the Weyland Mountains, realized that specimens from there matched the specimens supposedly from Karon and restricted the 
<typeStatus box="[299,349,1562,1583]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<emphasis box="[498,617,1562,1583]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">A.i. mayri</emphasis>
to the Weyland Mountains. It later became evident that van Renesse van Duivenbode had collectors working in the Weylands (
<bibRefCitation author="Stresemann" box="[135,466,1678,1700]" firstAuthor="Stresemann" page="145 - 146" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="144 - 147" refId="ref137685" refString="Stresemann, E. 1934. Vier neue Unterarten von Paradiesvogeln. Ornithologische Monatsberichte 42: 144 - 147." type="journal article" year="1934">Stresemann, 1934: 145–146</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hartert" page="167" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="165 - 240" refId="ref126298" refString="Hartert, E., K. Paludan, Lord Rothschild, and E. Stresemann. 1936. Die Vogel des Weyland- Gebirges und seines Vorlandes. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologisches Museum in Berlin 21: 165 - 240." type="journal article" year="1936">Hartert et al., 1936: 167</bibRefCitation>
, footnote 2); also see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1896" class="Aves" family="Cnemophilidae" genus="Loboparadisea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Loboparadisea sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1895" box="[361,646,1736,1759]" class="Aves" family="Paradisaeidae" genus="Astrapia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendidissima">
<emphasis box="[361,646,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Astrapia splendidissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mayr" box="[701,926,213,235]" firstAuthor="Mayr" page="183" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" refId="ref130342" refString="Mayr, E. 1941. List of New Guinea birds. New York: American Museum of Natural History, xi + 260 pp." type="book" year="1941">Mayr (1941: 183)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<emphasis box="[1064,1130,213,234]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">mayri</emphasis>
in the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Vis" authorityYear="1890" box="[789,978,242,264]" class="Aves" family="Ptilonorhynchidae" genus="Amblyornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macgregoriae">
<emphasis box="[789,978,242,264]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">A. macgregoriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, leaving 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schlegel" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1086,1228,242,264]" class="Aves" family="Ptilonorhynchidae" genus="Amblyornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inornatus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1228,242,264]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">A. inornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
monotypic.
</paragraph>
